module.exports = {"data":{"post":{"id":"/home/travis/build/simonagren/simonagren.github.io/content/posts/2018-11-25--part4-azurefunction/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/funcpnp4-9eba6bc91f2af79fc88248378c1ecef4-48538.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"pnp and azure func\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/funcpnp4-9eba6bc91f2af79fc88248378c1ecef4-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/funcpnp4-9eba6bc91f2af79fc88248378c1ecef4-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/funcpnp4-9eba6bc91f2af79fc88248378c1ecef4-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/funcpnp4-9eba6bc91f2af79fc88248378c1ecef4-48538.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>The posts in this series</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://simonagren.github.io/azurefunction-v2-pnpjs/\" target=\"_blank\">Part 1 - Azure Functions V2 + VS Code + PnPJs === true</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://simonagren.github.io/part2-azurefunction/\" target=\"_blank\">Part 2 - Azure Functions V2 + VS Code + PnPJs === true</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://simonagren.github.io/part3-azurefunction/\" target=\"_blank\">Part 3 - Azure Functions V2 + VS Code + PnPJs === true</a></li>\n<li>Part 4 - Azure Functions V2 + VS Code + PnPJs === true</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is the last post of this series and in this post, we will secure a Function App with Azure AD and create a custom connector. Then we will call the Azure Function from both Flow and SPFx</p>\n<p>When I started to implement this, the Azure subscription for my dev tenant expired. Then I was reminded that I could use my organizational MSDN subscription. But wait, if I build my Function Apps in the organizational tenant how could I access them in my dev tenant? This blog post ends up involving a multi-tenant scenario - which isn’t that bad really - it helped me refresh some knowledge.</p>\n<p>In the previous post, we discussed how to use the Azure Key vault to make our calls to SharePoint and the Microsoft Graph a little more secure. But we have not discussed how to secure our Azure functions themselves. In production, the anonymous access (alone) is a bad idea, since anyone could call your function. Another common scenario is to use “function” permission, which gives you a code that you would need to pass along in the query string of the URL. Even though this is more secure, anyone with that code could call the Azure Function - so I ended up securing the Function App via Azure AD while I kept the anonymous access to the Azure Function itself. </p>\n<p>Let’s get started.</p>\n<h2>Prerequisites</h2>\n<p>For this blog post, I assume you already have created a Function App. If you haven’t you could clone this <a href=\"https://github.com/simonagren/AzureADAzureFunction\" target=\"_blank\">solution</a> from my Github, and follow the steps in the readme file. </p>\n<h2>Secure the Function App via Azure AD</h2>\n<p>We will secure the Function App with Azure AD by creating an App Registration, make it a multi-tenant app, enable CORS for my Dev tenant and then consent as an Admin.</p>\n<h3>Register AD App for Azure Function in GUI</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Go to your Azure Portal and navigate to your Function App.</li>\n<li>Select “Platform Features” and then “Authentication/Authorization”</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/auth-46f8d5e387a8f7941fce2e8b3f92f2a3-b3ba2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 65.53438276719139%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"auth\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/auth-46f8d5e387a8f7941fce2e8b3f92f2a3-78f2b.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/auth-46f8d5e387a8f7941fce2e8b3f92f2a3-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/auth-46f8d5e387a8f7941fce2e8b3f92f2a3-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/auth-46f8d5e387a8f7941fce2e8b3f92f2a3-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/auth-46f8d5e387a8f7941fce2e8b3f92f2a3-ab4c4.jpg 1200w,\n/static/auth-46f8d5e387a8f7941fce2e8b3f92f2a3-b3ba2.jpg 1207w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Switch App Service Authentication to On, select “Log in with Azure Active Directory”, and select Azure Active Directory as the Authentication Provider</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/authentication-0a7120b4c777da38350b8d927b3eb032-4dcc2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 60.66252587991718%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"authentication\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/authentication-0a7120b4c777da38350b8d927b3eb032-78f2b.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/authentication-0a7120b4c777da38350b8d927b3eb032-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/authentication-0a7120b4c777da38350b8d927b3eb032-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/authentication-0a7120b4c777da38350b8d927b3eb032-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/authentication-0a7120b4c777da38350b8d927b3eb032-4dcc2.jpg 966w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Select “Express”, and “Create New AD App”, rename if you want to and then save everything.</li>\n<li>Make a note of the <code class=\"language-text\">Application ID</code>, we will use it later.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/newad-de4ca2aee15550093e8c0ce4f16cba6c-7a9a6.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 568px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"newad\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/newad-de4ca2aee15550093e8c0ce4f16cba6c-7a9a6.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/newad-de4ca2aee15550093e8c0ce4f16cba6c-7d049.jpg 200w,\n/static/newad-de4ca2aee15550093e8c0ce4f16cba6c-49a4a.jpg 400w,\n/static/newad-de4ca2aee15550093e8c0ce4f16cba6c-7a9a6.jpg 568w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>Change to Multi-tenant</h3>\n<p>Now there should be an “Authentication” link available directly in the overview of the Function App. Either press that Authentication link, or navigate the same way we did in the previous step via “Authentication/Authorization”.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Select Azure AD again from Application Providers -> Manage Application -> Settings -> Properties.</li>\n<li>Enter an App Id URI based on your tenant, mine was: <code class=\"language-text\">https://&lt;tenant&gt;.onmicrosoft.com/pnptesting</code></li>\n<li>Flip the Multi-tenant switch and then save!</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/multi-tenant-f93f24238c4e3d5a238c0a3317179101-a2374.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 637px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 137.8335949764521%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"multi-tenant\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/multi-tenant-f93f24238c4e3d5a238c0a3317179101-a2374.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/multi-tenant-f93f24238c4e3d5a238c0a3317179101-8cdb3.jpg 200w,\n/static/multi-tenant-f93f24238c4e3d5a238c0a3317179101-f8b37.jpg 400w,\n/static/multi-tenant-f93f24238c4e3d5a238c0a3317179101-a2374.jpg 637w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 637px) 100vw, 637px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Change the “Express” setting to Advanced, and then remove the Issuer Url. Press OK, then Save.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/advanced-d7eb38be81b61e3a792c0619b9b1d003-6a261.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 579px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 113.47150259067358%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"advanced\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/advanced-d7eb38be81b61e3a792c0619b9b1d003-6a261.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/advanced-d7eb38be81b61e3a792c0619b9b1d003-25878.jpg 200w,\n/static/advanced-d7eb38be81b61e3a792c0619b9b1d003-8633a.jpg 400w,\n/static/advanced-d7eb38be81b61e3a792c0619b9b1d003-6a261.jpg 579w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 579px) 100vw, 579px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>Fix CORS</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>In “Platform Features” again select CORS, and add the URL to your other tenant, mine was <code class=\"language-text\">https://agrendev.sharepoint.com</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cors-c0a8163e43656ee861b4be0fd19900e4-9d3f7.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 431px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 129.6983758700696%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"cors\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/cors-c0a8163e43656ee861b4be0fd19900e4-9d3f7.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cors-c0a8163e43656ee861b4be0fd19900e4-3b07c.jpg 200w,\n/static/cors-c0a8163e43656ee861b4be0fd19900e4-f1c92.jpg 400w,\n/static/cors-c0a8163e43656ee861b4be0fd19900e4-9d3f7.jpg 431w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 431px) 100vw, 431px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>Consent with a user from the other tenant</h3>\n<p>I opened a new window with the Chrome profile for my dev tenant. Then I navigated to the URL of the Function App (not the AD app) and was asked to consent. As I was logged in with the Admin account I was able to consent for the whole organization (sorry for the Swedish).</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/consent-3006ea22d484a84291d7d9115a625e52-0ac0c.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 594px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 125.58922558922558%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"consent\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/consent-3006ea22d484a84291d7d9115a625e52-0ac0c.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/consent-3006ea22d484a84291d7d9115a625e52-c74f0.jpg 200w,\n/static/consent-3006ea22d484a84291d7d9115a625e52-8ad2d.jpg 400w,\n/static/consent-3006ea22d484a84291d7d9115a625e52-0ac0c.jpg 594w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Now we could access this application in my dev tenant. The next step is to create a custom connector for Flow/PowerApps and then call the Azure Function via SPfx.</p>\n<h2>Create A Custom Connector</h2>\n<p>What I like to do is make an Azure AD Application in my dev tenant, with delegated permission to the App we created. So that is what we will do initially. Then we will create a custom connector from the UI in Flow.</p>\n<h3>Create AD Application and delegate permissions</h3>\n<p>Go to the Azure Portal of your consuming (in my case dev tenant), select Azure AD and the Application Registration.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Enter a name and a sign-on URL, then create</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/customconnector-b9af8830031486dbfd263d2a119616e1-28f07.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 511px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 168.88454011741683%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"customc\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/customconnector-b9af8830031486dbfd263d2a119616e1-28f07.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/customconnector-b9af8830031486dbfd263d2a119616e1-bd9c6.jpg 200w,\n/static/customconnector-b9af8830031486dbfd263d2a119616e1-cd9ce.jpg 400w,\n/static/customconnector-b9af8830031486dbfd263d2a119616e1-28f07.jpg 511w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 511px) 100vw, 511px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Go into settings, permissions, select permissions and then search for the name of your AD Application from the other tenant. In my case, it’s <code class=\"language-text\">pnptesting</code>.</li>\n<li>Delegate the permissions and select</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/delegatepermission-762ba21ce827226557c0663ff7ecd4f0-61e1c.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 51.58924205378973%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"delegatepermission\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/delegatepermission-762ba21ce827226557c0663ff7ecd4f0-78f2b.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/delegatepermission-762ba21ce827226557c0663ff7ecd4f0-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/delegatepermission-762ba21ce827226557c0663ff7ecd4f0-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/delegatepermission-762ba21ce827226557c0663ff7ecd4f0-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/delegatepermission-762ba21ce827226557c0663ff7ecd4f0-ab4c4.jpg 1200w,\n/static/delegatepermission-762ba21ce827226557c0663ff7ecd4f0-bc99b.jpg 1600w,\n/static/delegatepermission-762ba21ce827226557c0663ff7ecd4f0-61e1c.jpg 1636w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Press “Grant Permissions” and ok.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/granted-ee234ea33ea6209736fa547208751bac-daccd.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 754px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 68.43501326259947%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"granted\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/granted-ee234ea33ea6209736fa547208751bac-daccd.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/granted-ee234ea33ea6209736fa547208751bac-9d0e2.jpg 200w,\n/static/granted-ee234ea33ea6209736fa547208751bac-f2980.jpg 400w,\n/static/granted-ee234ea33ea6209736fa547208751bac-daccd.jpg 754w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 754px) 100vw, 754px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Go into keys, create a new key. Make a note of the <code class=\"language-text\">key value</code> and the <code class=\"language-text\">application id</code> of this app.\nMake sure to leave the window open, since we’re going to change the reply URL.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Create a Custom Connector in Flow</h3>\n<p>You could use the Wizard directly in Flow/PowerApps, import an OpenAPI (swagger) file, or a Postman collection.\nMy experience revolves around creating collections in Postman and importing them, so for this post, we will use the Wizard in the UI. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Navigate to the Flow portal, under data select custom connectors. Then select “Create custom connector”</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/createcc-b32d077822d099657d0a059b6ba398c1-63130.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 550px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75.81818181818181%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"createcc\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/createcc-b32d077822d099657d0a059b6ba398c1-63130.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/createcc-b32d077822d099657d0a059b6ba398c1-202ec.jpg 200w,\n/static/createcc-b32d077822d099657d0a059b6ba398c1-900dc.jpg 400w,\n/static/createcc-b32d077822d099657d0a059b6ba398c1-63130.jpg 550w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Enter the URL to your function app (not the HttpTrigger) as “Host”, then move to security</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cc-f4af0fb2752667ed7010fd9029224e34-f8d45.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 84.26842684268428%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"cc\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/cc-f4af0fb2752667ed7010fd9029224e34-78f2b.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cc-f4af0fb2752667ed7010fd9029224e34-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/cc-f4af0fb2752667ed7010fd9029224e34-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/cc-f4af0fb2752667ed7010fd9029224e34-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/cc-f4af0fb2752667ed7010fd9029224e34-f8d45.jpg 909w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Select Oauth 2.0, Azure Active Directory as the Identity provider, enter the client Id and secret of your newly created app.</li>\n<li>The resource URL is the ID of the Azure AD app we created in the other tenant, the one I told you to make a note of the ID.</li>\n<li>Save now, and you will receive a redirect URL.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ccsettings-7dfe375819e79c78e733a4ed23bf9485-8f86d.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 664px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 111.14457831325302%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"ccsettings\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ccsettings-7dfe375819e79c78e733a4ed23bf9485-8f86d.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ccsettings-7dfe375819e79c78e733a4ed23bf9485-7dcd7.jpg 200w,\n/static/ccsettings-7dfe375819e79c78e733a4ed23bf9485-4d79f.jpg 400w,\n/static/ccsettings-7dfe375819e79c78e733a4ed23bf9485-8f86d.jpg 664w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 664px) 100vw, 664px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Go back into the <code class=\"language-text\">Azure Portal</code> and change the Reply Url to the one you received in the custom connector.</li>\n<li>Go back into the <code class=\"language-text\">Custom connector</code>, and move on to definition.</li>\n<li>Add a new Action, I just named everything GetLists</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/action-1120412bca260bb1913cf0f70516c238-317c2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 704px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 63.92045454545454%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"action\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/action-1120412bca260bb1913cf0f70516c238-317c2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/action-1120412bca260bb1913cf0f70516c238-d983c.jpg 200w,\n/static/action-1120412bca260bb1913cf0f70516c238-70f29.jpg 400w,\n/static/action-1120412bca260bb1913cf0f70516c238-317c2.jpg 704w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 704px) 100vw, 704px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Under request, select Import from sample.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Select “POST”, and enter something like this in the body</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\">\n      <pre class=\"language-json\"><code class=\"language-json\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">\"site\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"test3\"</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Create the Connection and move on to test. </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We will have to wait a couple of minutes for it to be provisioned, so go get some coffee.\nAfter, you could test the connector in the test operation.</p>\n<h2>Test the Connection in Flow</h2>\n<p>Let’s try this in Flow.\nI’m adding a manual trigger and then the custom connector.\nFilling in the properties that we need.\nThis Azure Function creates an Item in a custom list - very basic.</p>\n<p>As you can see we’ve created an item in SharePoint now.</p>\n<h2>Call the Azure Function from SPFx</h2>\n<p>UPDATE:\nI added the link to two articles that involve similar things that I’m doing in this post.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Waldek Mastykarz wrote a good blog post on this subject about how you could solve the API Permissions easier with Office365 CLI <a href=\"https://blog.mastykarz.nl/grant-api-permissions-office-365-cli/\">here</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Vesa Juvonen, Waldek Mastykarz, Linda Caputo and Chris Kent have written a good post <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sharepoint/dev/spfx/use-aadhttpclient-enterpriseapi\">here</a> about similar things that I do in this post. </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p>So I’ve created a simple SPFx web part <a href=\"https://github.com/simonagren/SPFxAzureFunction\">solution</a> that you could clone from my Github.</p>\n<p>Follow the readme and replace it with your variables in the code. In this web part, we are requesting API Permissions.</p>\n<h3>Package solution</h3>\n<p>Package the solution with the following commands. The file will end up in the <code class=\"language-text\">sharepoint\\solution</code> folder.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\">\n      <pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">gulp bundle --ship\ngulp package-solution --ship</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3>Deploy the solution</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>I usually right-click in VS Code and choose to reveal in Explorer.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/reveal-04181b9785b01b0b4b6745bed7971f21-2cccd.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 561px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 109.80392156862746%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"reveal\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/reveal-04181b9785b01b0b4b6745bed7971f21-2cccd.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/reveal-04181b9785b01b0b4b6745bed7971f21-28b71.jpg 200w,\n/static/reveal-04181b9785b01b0b4b6745bed7971f21-b1664.jpg 400w,\n/static/reveal-04181b9785b01b0b4b6745bed7971f21-2cccd.jpg 561w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 561px) 100vw, 561px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Copy the path to the folder</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Navigate to your App catalog. Then later in the browser when I upload I  just paste the path in the upper pane then select the package.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/upload-45da72f690a493136457b8529d64be7c-fe374.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 69.0909090909091%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"upload\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/upload-45da72f690a493136457b8529d64be7c-78f2b.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/upload-45da72f690a493136457b8529d64be7c-dce19.jpg 200w,\n/static/upload-45da72f690a493136457b8529d64be7c-c1413.jpg 400w,\n/static/upload-45da72f690a493136457b8529d64be7c-78f2b.jpg 800w,\n/static/upload-45da72f690a493136457b8529d64be7c-fe374.jpg 1045w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Deploy</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Test the web part</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Open a page add the web part.</li>\n<li>Now you should see all your SharePoint Lists.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/webpartresult-c6e23efeb51d02885a5148b8389fb30d-6563d.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 660px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 92.57575757575756%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"result\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/webpartresult-c6e23efeb51d02885a5148b8389fb30d-6563d.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/webpartresult-c6e23efeb51d02885a5148b8389fb30d-af3ac.jpg 200w,\n/static/webpartresult-c6e23efeb51d02885a5148b8389fb30d-04ddd.jpg 400w,\n/static/webpartresult-c6e23efeb51d02885a5148b8389fb30d-6563d.jpg 660w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Thank you</h2>\n<p>Thank you for following along in this series.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/part4-azurefunction/","prefix":"2018-11-25"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Part 4 - Azure Functions V2 + VS Code + PnPJs === true","author":"Simon Ågren","category":null,"tags":["sharepoint","pnp","azurefunctions","nodejs"],"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/funcpnp4-9eba6bc91f2af79fc88248378c1ecef4-160fa.png"}}}}},"authornote":{"id":"/home/travis/build/simonagren/simonagren.github.io/content/parts/author.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","html":"<p><strong>Simon Ågren</strong> Passionate about SharePoint and Office365. Solution Architect working as a consultant for Sogeti in Umeå, Sweden.</p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"facebook":{"appId":"2263145610597628"}}}},"pathContext":{"slug":"/part4-azurefunction/","prev":{"id":"/home/travis/build/simonagren/simonagren.github.io/content/posts/2018-11-20--part3-azurefunction/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","fields":{"slug":"/part3-azurefunction/","prefix":"2018-11-20"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Part 3 - Azure Functions V2 + VS Code + PnPJs === true","category":null,"tags":["sharepoint","pnp","azurefunctions","nodejs"]}},"next":{"id":"/home/travis/build/simonagren/simonagren.github.io/content/posts/2019-02-07--sp-starter-xml-links/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","fields":{"slug":"/sp-starter-xml-links/","prefix":"2019-02-07"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Extending My Links in SharePoint Starter Kit","category":null,"tags":["sharepoint","pnp"]}}}}


